thread.title: Australian share market is higher

author: AAP
title: Australian share market is higher
text:
THE Australian share market has opened higher, after international markets gained amid respite from volatile Chinese markets, closed for a holiday and ahead of a US jobs market report likely to shape the Federal Reserve’s interest rate decision.
At 1010 AEST on Friday, the benchmark S&P/ASX200 index was up 10.4 points, or 0.21 per cent, at 5,038.2, while the broader All Ordinaries index was up 8.9 points, or 0.18 per cent, at 5,057.6.
On the ASX 24, the September share price index futures contract was up 10 points at 5,015, with 8,822 contracts traded. AAP cdh
At 0645 AEST on Friday, the September share price index futures contract was up 18 points at 5,023.
Locally, in economic news on Friday, the Australian Bureau of Statistics releases July’s overseas arrivals and departure figures. And, the ING releases its report for women in financial services.
Meanwhile, the three-day Africa Down Under Conference wraps up in Perth.
No equities news is expected on Thursday.
In Australia, the market on Thursday sharply lower, led downwards by the big banks as investors decided to put their money elsewhere.
The benchmark S&P/ASX200 index was down 73.7 points, or 1.44 per cent, at 5,027.8 points.
The broader All Ordinaries index was down 70.7 points, or 1.38 per cent, at 5,048.7 points.
